	<h2>Vehicle Investigations Tips</h2>
        <p><b>The Vehicle Investigations search provides information on vehicle registrations as recorded by state agencies. Search results cover automobiles in addition to boats, trailers, RVs, and other assets registered with the Department of Motor Vehicles.</b></p>
        <p>&nbsp;<br>Find a vehicle record using one or more of the following search techniques. Please note that the Vehicle Investigations Search includes data from various data providers.  Some data providers may require a Name and Street Address to be included in your search.  If you conduct a search without Name and Address and do not receive a match (or the match you were expecting), you may want to run another search including Name, Street Address, Zip Code or Name, Street Address and City/State.<br>&nbsp;</p>
        <ol id="font81">
          <li>Search using a VIN. The Vehicle Identification Number generally consists of seventeen characters that are used to uniquely identify a motor vehicle.<br><br></li>
          <li>Search by an individual's Name, Street Address, City, and State or Name, Street Address, and Zip.<br><br></li>
          <li>Search by Company Name and State.<br><br></li>
          <li>Search by Address, City, and State. This returns records using that address.<br><br></li>
          <li>Search using the vehicle's Tag Number and State.<br><br></li>
        </ol>
